    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawings or prints, typically profile portraits, made by tracing a profile from a shadow cast by the sitter using a physionotrace, a mechanical instrument invented in 1784 by the French musician and portraitist Gilles-Louis Chrétien.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
